SECTION 11. The catch line to G.S. 90-210.25 reads as rewritten:
"§ 90-210.25. Licensing.Requirements for all applicants."
SECTION 12. G.S. 90-210.25, as amended by this act, reads as rewritten:
"§ 90-210.25. Requirements for all applicants.
(a) Qualifications, Examinations, Resident Traineeship and Licensure. –An applicant for
a license, permit, or resident traineeship bears the burden of substantiating to the satisfaction of
the Board that the applicant meets the qualifications for the license, permit, or resident
traineeship. An applicant must do all of the following when submitting an application:
(1) Submit the application on a form provided by the Board.
(2) Sign the application under oath, attesting to the accuracy of the application.
(3) Consent to a criminal history background check. If the applicant is a business
entity, any owner, partner, manager, member, operator, or officer of the entity
must also consent to a criminal history background check. Refusal to consent
is grounds to deny the application.
(4) Pay any required fee.
…."
