(3) Be able to provide protection for the health and safety of reduction facility
personnel.
(4) Be easily identifiable. The covering of the reduction container shall contain
all of the following information:
a. The name of the decedent.
b. The date of death.
c. The sex of the decedent.
d. The age of the decedent at death.
